	id="Exa_DistancePoints">
	<texsupport href="../LinearAlgebraTeXSupport.xml"/>
	<title>Examples of Computing the Distance Between Points</title>
	<caption>Distance between Points - Example</caption>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the distance between the points <latex>R(4,-1,11)</latex> and <latex>Q(-2,6,4)</latex> in <latex>\RNr[3]</latex>.  
			</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>According to the general formula for the distance between two points, we find</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
			       		\aligned
 					\Dstnc{R}{Q}\ &=\ \sqrt{(-2-4)^2+(6-(-1))^2+(4-11)^2} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{36+49+49} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{134}
 					\endaligned
 					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>Note that we obtain the same answer if we reverse the roles of the points <latex>P</latex> and <latex>Q</latex>:</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
			       		\aligned
 					\Dstnc{Q}{R}\ &=\ \sqrt{(4-(-2))^2+((-1)-6)^2+(11-4)^2} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{36+49+49} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{134}
 					\endaligned
 					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</answer>
	</showme>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the distance between the points <latex>A(6,0,3,-1,5)</latex> and <latex>B(1,-2,3,0,6)</latex> in <latex>\RNr[5]</latex>.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>According to the general formula for the distance between two points, we find</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
			       		\aligned
 					\Dstnc{B}{A}\ &=\ \sqrt{(6-1)^2+(0-(-2))^2+(3-3)^2 + ((-1)-0)^2 + (5-6)^2} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{25+4+0+1+1} \\
 					&=\ \sqrt{31}
 					\endaligned
 					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</answer>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>